<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 9: LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTER AND
        COOLER - LUBRICATING OIL PUMP - ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="6">
        <title>ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new oil seal into the lubricating oil pump housing as follows, use
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE3004A</emph>:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply gasket eliminator #515 to the O.D. of the oil seal.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Slip oil seal into installing tool.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Press the seal into the oil pump housing so the front of the seal is flush with the
                    front of the oil pump housing (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600910">9.10</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-Ring on the front cover, then install the housing plate (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600911">9.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600910" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5211" filename="../figeg5/EG5211.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.10 Installing Oil Seal Into Lubricating Oil Pump</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600911" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5096" filename="../figeg5/EG5096.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.11 Installing New O-Ring And Housing Plate</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">1. O-Ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">2. Oil Pump Plate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the inner rotor and oil slinger onto the crankshaft gear spline (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600912">9.12</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>OIL SLINGER FITS WITH THE CONCAVE SHAPE FACING OUT.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the inner rotor installed, tap in the woodruff key with a hammer (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600913">9.13</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the outer rotor with clean engine oil and install rotor into the oil pump housing
                (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600914">9.14</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-Ring into the housing groove and align housing dowel pins with mounting
                locations. Install oil pump housing to front cover (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600914">9.14</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate oil seal prior to installation.</para>
            <figure id="ef1600912" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5095" filename="../figeg5/EG5095.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.12 Installing Inner Rotor And Slinger</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600913" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5094" filename="../figeg5/EG5094.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.13 Installing Woodruff Key</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600914" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg6172" filename="../figeg6/EG6172.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.14 Installing Oil Lubricating Pump Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the six capscrews (two short capscrews are located at the two and three o'clock
                positions) to secure oil pump housing to the front cover. Tighten the capscrews to the standard torque
                value (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600915">9.15</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the vibration damper as specified in
                <emph type="bold">"Section 7"</emph>.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600915" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5091" filename="../figeg5/EG5091.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.15 Securing Oil Pump Housing Mounting Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
